# Environment Variables for React Inventory System

## Frontend Google OAuth Configuration (REQUIRED)
# Used by the frontend for Google OAuth login
# Create OAuth credentials at: https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 1. Create OAuth 2.0 Client ID (Web application)
# 2. Add authorized redirect URIs:
#    - http://localhost:5173 (local dev)
#    - https://your-domain.vercel.app (production)
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id.apps.googleusercontent.com

## Backend Google OAuth Configuration (REQUIRED)
# Used by the API to verify Google tokens
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_google_client_secret

## Frontend API Backend URL
# Local dev: Uses vite proxy (see vite.config.ts) - routes /api to localhost:3000
# Production: Set to your Vercel domain
VITE_BACKEND_URL=https://your-domain.vercel.app

## Supabase Database (REQUIRED)
# Create a free account at: https://supabase.com
# 1. Create a new project
# 2. Go to Settings → API to find these keys
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key (public key)
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_supabase_service_role_key (secret key)

## Node Environment
NODE_ENV=production

# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 
# 1. Local Development:
#    - Copy this file to .env.local
#    - Fill in your actual credentials
#    - Run: npm run dev
#    - Access at: http://localhost:5173
#
# 2. Vercel Production:
#    - Add all variables to Vercel dashboard Settings → Environment Variables
#    - Apply to Production & Preview
#    - Push to GitHub to trigger deployment
#    - Vercel will use these vars when building and running serverless functions

